## When elevating permissions for system operations

System operations (bootstrap, login/registration flows) that need to write permission-protected entities must run under a service account:

```typescript
import {ModuleBE_Permissions, ServiceAccountId_Bootstrap} from '@nu-art/permissions-backend';

await ModuleBE_Permissions.runAsServiceAccount(ServiceAccountId_Bootstrap, async () => {
	await ModuleBE_PermissionRoleDB.set.all([...]);
});
```

The `bootstrap-admin` SA is registered by default with `permissions:admin`. Service accounts are defined in module config:

```typescript
type ServiceAccountConfig = {
	readonly scopes: string[];      // e.g. ['permissions:admin']
	readonly enabled: boolean;
	readonly systemOnly: boolean;   // if true, cannot be used within a user request context
};
```

**Do not bypass permissions in any other way.** No flags, no middleware skipping, no direct MemKey manipulation. `runAsServiceAccount` is the only elevation mechanism.

---

## When integrating permissions into an app

### Backend

1. Add `ModulePackBE_Permissions` to the app backend module pack.
2. Add `ModuleBE_PermissionsAssert.LoadPermissionsMiddleware` to the HTTP server middleware chain.
3. Wire scope permissions on your DB modules using `wireScopePermission` or `wireEntityPermissions`.
4. Decorate API handlers with `@RequirePermission`.

### Frontend

Add `ModulePackFE_Permissions` to the Thunder builder:

```typescript
import {ModulePackFE_Permissions} from '@nu-art/permissions-frontend';

new Thunder(config)
	.addModulePack(ModulePackFE_Permissions)
	.build();
```

This enables IDB caching and smart-sync for all three permission entity types (scope, role, user).

### Reacting to permission data changes in UI

Extend `ComponentSync` and implement the relevant `On*Updated` interfaces:

```typescript
import {ComponentSync} from '@nu-art/thunder-widgets';
import type {OnPermissionUserUpdated} from '@nu-art/permissions-frontend';

class MyComponent
	extends ComponentSync<{}, State>
	implements OnPermissionUserUpdated {

	__onPermissionUserUpdated() {
		this.reDeriveState();
	}
}
```

### Client-side permission checks

```typescript
import {ModuleFE_PermissionsAssert} from '@nu-art/permissions-frontend';

if (ModuleFE_PermissionsAssert.hasScopeAccess(PermissionScope_Topics, 'write')) {
	// show edit UI
}
```

