## System roles (do not create manually)

The bootstrap process creates and overwrites these on every startup:

| Role | ID derivation | Purpose |
|------|---------------|---------|
| **Default** | `md5('app/default')` | Assigned to all users; scope entries collected from modules via `CollectDefaultScopeValues` |
| **Permissions Admin** | `md5('permissions/admin')` | Highest scope value for every registered scope; grants full control |

Both have `system: true` — they can only be modified by the bootstrap service account. Do not create or modify system roles outside of the bootstrap process.

---

## DB entities

| Entity | DB key | Collection |
|--------|--------|------------|
| `DB_PermissionScope` | `permissions--scope` | `permissions--scopes` |
| `DB_PermissionRole` | `permissions--role` | `permissions--roles` |
| `DB_PermissionUser` | `permissions--user` | `permissions--users` |

All share the `permissions` IDB group on the frontend.

---

## Naming conventions

| Artifact | Convention |
|----------|-----------|
| Scope constant | `PermissionScope_<Domain>` |
| Scope definition file | `permission-scope.ts` in the concept's shared package |
| Scope entity IDs | `permissionScopeId(key, value)` — deterministic via md5, do not wrap |
| Role IDs | `RoleId_<Name>` derived via `stringToUniqueId<DatabaseDef_PermissionRole["dbKey"]>(md5('context/name'))` |
| Service account IDs | `ServiceAccountId_<Name>` string constants |

---

## Forbidden patterns

- **Never use the old domain/access-level model** (`PermissionDomain`, `PermissionAccessLevel`, `CollectPermissionsProjects`). Legacy infrastructure — do not use in application code.
- **Never define scopes in backend-only packages.** Both FE and BE must access the scope registry.
- **Never create trivial ID wrapper functions.** Use `stringToUniqueId<DatabaseDef_*["dbKey"]>(id)` directly at the call site.
- **Never bypass permissions** with flags, env vars, or direct MemKey writes. Use `runAsServiceAccount`.
- **Never modify system roles** from app-level code. They are bootstrap-only.

